# Crawler Server Environment Variables

# Indexer Server IP Address (or Frontend IP if co-located)
# Used to connect to the Indexer API (port 8081)
# Get IP: ssh to Indexer/Frontend Server, run `curl http://checkip.amazonaws.com`
INDEXER_IP=203.0.113.10
# Fallback to FRONTEND_IP if INDEXER_IP not set (for backward compatibility)
FRONTEND_IP=203.0.113.10

# API key for authenticating with Indexer
# MUST match the INDEXER_API_KEY from Frontend/Indexer Server
# Get this by running on Frontend Server: cat ~/web-search/deployment/frontend/.env | grep INDEXER_API_KEY
INDEXER_API_KEY=change-this-to-match-frontend-api-key

# Note: Redis is now included in the Crawler's docker-compose.yml
# The Crawler uses its own local Redis instance (redis://redis:6379/0)
# Crawler sends indexed pages to Indexer service (port 8081) via HTTP API
